  "prompt": "What book would you recommend for young adults to read to help them in life?",
  "response": "I recommend \"The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People\" by Stephen R. Covey. Although it\u2019s not specifically categorized as a young adult book, its principles are highly relevant for young adults navigating key life transitions. Covey provides a framework for personal effectiveness, focusing on habits that promote proactive behavior, prioritization, and synergy in relationships. The insights on time management, goal-setting, and interpersonal effectiveness can be incredibly beneficial for young adults as they encounter new challenges in their personal and professional lives.\n\nAnother great option is \"The Alchemist\" by Paulo Coelho, which tells the story of a young shepherd's journey to discover his personal legend. This allegorical novel encourages readers to pursue their dreams and listen to their hearts, offering valuable life lessons about perseverance and self-discovery.\n\nBoth books can provide young adults with useful perspectives and tools to navigate life\u2019s challenges.",
